Class AIComponent

  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AIButtonActions, AICheckBoxActions, AIComboBoxActions, AIComponentActions, AIEditBoxActions, AIListViewActions, AIMiscActions, AITextActions

    public class AIComponent
extends AISearchBase
    Used to hold checkbox test step definitions for gherkin feature files. CheckBoxes are generally found by matching the Criteria.

      • setText

        protected void setText(java.lang.String libName,
                       boolean isCharacter,
                       java.lang.String text)
                throws SeleniumPlusException
        Clear the content of Component box first, and then enter the text into it.
        Parameters:
        libName - String, the concrete Component name of class, which calls 'setText()' method, like 'EditBox', 'ComboBox'.
        isCharacter - boolean, if true, the text'll be treated as plain text, without special key dealing; if false, the text'll be treated as special keys.
        text - String, the content to be entered into Component box.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException

      • process

        protected void process(java.lang.String action,
                       java.lang.String criteria,
                       int nthMatched,
                       java.util.List<java.lang.String> parameters,
                       java.lang.String customerType)
                throws SAFSException
        Handle the SAFS Keywords against the a component matching the provided textlabel.
        Parameters:
        action - String, the action to perform
        criteria - String, the search-conditions helping to find the component
        it can be the 'text label' associated with (or near) the component
        it can be the xpath (start with prefix XPATH=) to identify the component
        it can be the css-selector (start with prefix CSS=) to find the component
        It can be map-item (plain-text, SAFS-recognition-string) defined in a map file.
        nthMatched - int, 1-based index, the Nth matched component if there are multiple components matching the search criteria.
        parameters - List, the parameters required by the action
        customerType - String, the customer-defined type for matching component.
        Throws:
        SAFSException - if target object cannot be found, or the keyword is not supported, or any exception has been met.
